Sentencas: The search for cathode materials with high oxygen reduction reactions activity is a key step toward reducing the operation temperature of solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: BaFe0.6Ce0.1Co0.3O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: We report a novel perovskite-type BaFe0.6Ce0.1Co0.3O3-delta (BFCC) cathode, which exhibits outstanding activity for oxygen reduction reactions and yields low interfacial resistances, e.g., 0.113 Omega cm(2) at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: BaFe0.6Ce0.1Co0.3O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SEM results show that BFCC is chemically, thermally compatible with Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) at operation temperatures.
Titulo: BaFe0.6Ce0.1Co0.3O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The tri-layer single cells of Ni-SDC vertical bar SDC vertical bar BFCC are operated from 500 to 650 degrees C with humidified hydrogen (similar to 3% H2O) as fuel and oxygen as oxidant.
Titulo: BaFe0.6Ce0.1Co0.3O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It shows excellent power densities of 1422mWcm(-2) at 650 degrees C and 1086mWcm(-2) at 600 degrees C. Preliminary results demonstrate that the BFCC is a promising cathode material for reduced-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: BaFe0.6Ce0.1Co0.3O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
